My girlfriend had the New York strip which looked like a brontosaurus leg. She never eats all her food n We had NO leftovers to take home. We ate it ALL! Left the plates clean... The waiters were so cool... They deserved every bit of the tip they received. I wish I could've left more... I will certainly be back... I've definitely found my new spot... Loved this place. I came here with a friend on a Saturday night around 7pm and we were seated right away. The way they greeted us was so friendly that I had to question whether I'd been there before and they remembered me (I wasn't lol).  We ordered the Malbec empanadas, Mollejas, and the the biste chorizo. The empanadas were delicious and I would highly recommend. I had never had mollejas before and was not familiar with what it was; it tasted like scrambled eggs. My friend didn't care for it (it gets just a shrug from me). My chorizo steak was cooked perfectly! I asked for medium well and got medium well. It was very tasty. I also ordered the asparagus and french fries; they were good as well. For dessert we got the dulce de leche crepe; very very tasty but not overly sweet. At 8pm they had live music; the singer was incredible. Overall, great experience, every single staff member was very friendly and very attentive, and I would be happy to go back again.

A nice little restaurant that packs a big flavorful Argentinian punch. I took family and close friends there for my moms birthday. It was a big party and they were able to accommodate us with out any issues. Just call ahead and make reservations for big parties. Let’s get to the nitty gritty. I’ve been back twice since the first time I visited and the food hasn’t disappointed during any of the visits. I had the churrasco and it was delicious. My only minor disappointment would be that it was missing the green jalapeño pepper all Argentinian steaks come with. My next choice was the Ribeye steak and once again it didn’t disappoint.  As for cocktails. The sangria was delicious. It was perfectly sweet and dangerous. On Saturday evenings they have two guys singing traditionally Spanish songs, and modern, with their guitars and kept a nice mellow vibe throughout the evening. All the servers where extremely nice, and able to answer any question and made great suggestions when asked. I would have to say. If my mom, who is a stickler when it come to Latin food, walked out satisfied. And my lil son feed and entertained during dinner with music. This place is wonderful. Will be back in the near future.
